 Career History



Director, President & Chief Executive Officer of the Company & Micron Products, Inc

                                    2013 - Current                


Micron Solutions, Inc.


                  Micron Solutions, Inc. is a diversified contract manufacturing organization that produces engineered, medical device technologies requiring precision machining and injection molding. The company also manufactures components, devices and equipment for military, law enforcement, industrial and consumer product applications. It engages in the production and sale of silver/silver chloride coated and conductive resin sensors used as consumable component parts in the manufacture of integrated disposable electrophysiological sensors. Micron Solutions was founded in 1981 and is headquartered in Fitchburg, MA.                




President & Chief Executive Officer

                                    1995 - Current                


Micron Products, Inc.


                  Micron Products, Inc., a subsidiary of Micron Solutions, Inc., is a company headquartered in Fitchburg, MA, that manufactures and distributes silver plated and non-silver plated conductive resin sensors used in the manufacture of disposable electrodes.                




President & Chief Executive Officer

                                    Current                


RMDDxUSA Corp.


                  RMDDxUSA Corp., part of Micron Solutions, Inc., is a company headquartered in the United States that manufactures medical imaging devices.                




President & Chief Executive Officer

                                    Current                


Corazonix Corp.


                  Part of Micron Solutions, Inc., Corazonix Corp. is an American company located in Oklahoma City, OK, that develops electrocardiography products. The firm was founded by David E. Albert. Corazonix Corp. was acquired by Micron Solutions, Inc. on 16 Nov 93.                




Controller

                                    Prior                


Kervick Enterprises, Inc.


                  Kervick Enterprises, Inc. operates as a holding company. It supplies to the medical, aerospace, nuclear, petrochemical and industrial markets. Its products include drop and upset high temperature aluminum, stainless steel, iron and steel forgings. The company is headquartered in Worcester, MA.                





